      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "I would suggest looking at `sudo dmesg | less` output. Search for `oom-kill`, before that there will be full process list at that point, with information about memory consumption for each process. But it's likely a lot of RAM used by GUI stuff (as bitcoin-qt was mentioned). For such memory constrained devices, no-GUI command-line only would be better.",
